Package com.example.phonebook

Class PhoneBook

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.phonebook.PhoneBook
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable
    public class PhoneBook
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.AutoCloseable
    Phone book implementation backed by SQLite database. Constructor and all methods throw PhoneBookStorageException in case of a database failure.

    • Constructor Detail

      • PhoneBook

        public PhoneBook​(java.lang.String dbPath)
        Create new PhoneBook with an open connection to database file named dbPath. Path can be anything that SQLite-jdbc library accepts in connection string after 'jdbc:sqlite:', for example ':memory:'.

    • Method Detail

      • addEntry

        public void addEntry​(java.lang.String name,
                     java.lang.String number)
        Add an entry with given name and number. Does nothing if the entry is already present.

      • getNumbersByName

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getNumbersByName​(java.lang.String name)
        Returns a list with numbers corresponding to the given name. Numbers are sorted lexicographically.

      • getNamesByNumber

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getNamesByNumber​(java.lang.String number)
        Returns a list with names corresponding to the given number. Names are sorted lexicographically.

      • getEntries

        public java.util.List<PhoneBook.Entry> getEntries()
        Returns a list with entries present in the phone book. Entries are sorted by name, and then by number if names are equal.

      • deleteEntry

        public void deleteEntry​(java.lang.String name,
                        java.lang.String number)
        Deletes an entry with given name and number. Does nothing if no such entry exist.

      • updateName

        public void updateName​(java.lang.String currentName,
                       java.lang.String currentNumber,
                       java.lang.String newName)
        Update name in entry with given name and number. Does nothing if no such entry exist. If the operation creates an entry equivalent to an already existing entry, they are merged.

      • updateNumber

        public void updateNumber​(java.lang.String currentName,
                         java.lang.String currentNumber,
                         java.lang.String newNumber)
        Update number in entry with given name and number. Does nothing if no such entry exist. If the operation creates an entry equivalent to an already existing entry, they are merged.

        Delete all entries in the phone book.
